.TH "pm_runtime_drop_link" 9 "pm_runtime_drop_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pm_runtime_drop_link \- Prepare for device link removal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pm_runtime_drop_link
.BI "(struct device_link *link "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
Device link going away.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Drop the link count of the consumer end of \fIlink\fP and decrement the supplier
device's runtime PM usage counter as many times as needed to drop all of the
PM runtime reference to it from the consumer.
